With only 2 shows left of this European Leg, we thought we would give you a little taste of how we got here!
.
When @robertraab called us about this gig, he asked us to sing a few of Lizzo’s singles so she could hear our voices and see our faces ASAP! Of course we were all in different cities/states, so we ran to some quiet rooms, recorded one by one and sent one another our videos so we could match the timing as best we could… then we had our videos put together so she could hear us collectively and see us TOGETHER (even though we weren’t physically 😩😂).
.
Having YEARSSSS of singing together under our belts, from church, to @gleeofficial , to @girlbluewho , and MORE, we were so excited to do this and stoked to get to tour together! 💜 
.
We’re just out here working hard, having fun, and prayerfully impacting lives in the BEST WAY! 💜.
.

Wow!!! Chantal and I had a hot date last night and it was awesome!!! My wife @chantal_stevenson got me tickets as a Christmas present to the @newedition @keithsweat GUY @teddyriley1 @damionhall_guy @thelegendaryaaronhall and @therealtank Jay V. Legacy Tour in Atlanta last night. I went as a fan and was overwhelmed with pure joy. Watching my hero’s do there thing was an emotional and joyful experience. The only way as a little boy to be able to see New Edition in concert was to ask my mother to allow us to go to the skating ring in Orlando. I don’t think she ever knew that the skating ring would have concerts but she allowed us to go. I was surprised that I still knew a lot of their choreography. I’ve always felt that I was always working hard to be the 7th member of NE. I’ve never seen Guy perform together as a group since they started as group until last night. I was a fan then and still a fan to this very day. Keith Sweat got hits and put on an amazing show. Tank need I say more is the future of R&B. He’s in my opinion this generation of our Luther Vandross. What a night!!! #GodIs

@russ ALL THE CREDITS AND FEATURES FOR SANTIAGO
What a collaborative effort this album was. I'll try to keep it short but the founder of a producer collective @odd.status lived next door to my manager. His mom would pitch him to my manager and after enough persistence Milan played me some of the beats. At first they weren't "there" but another year or so went by and I was like "yea get these guys to the house." Flew out a bunch of young upcoming producers who really only had been making beats for YouTube at that point.
One of them was my cousin. I also called 2 of the illest writers and minds I know, @bibibourelly @rexxliferaj to come and hang out for the weekend. Long story short everyone ended up stayin a month. Bibi, this album really doesn't happen without you. I feel like we wrote damn near the whole thing together. Your energy, vision and voice is sprinkled throughout and I'm just super happy we got to connect and make this. You brought in @melaniefaye who is one of the most insane guitarists and she played the guitar part for
"Fatima" right when she walked in..then the bass line
After makin the album I essentially sent the whole thing to @aaronxparis and he along with his network of collaborators completely elevated SANTIAGO. They added choirs and orchestral elements and did all the transitions in between songs. Without them, SANTIAGO is not what it is. In the final hour, I had an idea for a song called "Fraud" and it's been a lifelong dream of mine to get @justinnozuka on a song. His voice is a 1 of 1. He sent over an idea super quick and it was INSANE and ended up bein what you hear on the album now. A big part of my brand has been self sufficiency and "do it myself" but that was always out of survival and necessity...I'm proud that I can do certain things myself but I simply didn't have a choice back when I made that song.
Now I have access to some of the most talented people in the world and I'm grateful all of you helped make this album come to fruition. Without y'all, SANTIAGO would not be what it is AT ALL. If there's anyone I'm forgetting in the credits please lemme know!! THANK YOU #GodIs

Words cannot describe how much being in Africa has been good to my soul. I know that there’s so much for me to learn about African culture and today opened my eyes, my heart and my soul to what I witnessed today. We were blessed to watch @thanga.choir perform for us. With every step that they took connected with my heartbeat to the rhythm of the drum. Their angelic voices were powerful and sweet which cut through the depths of my soul. I had to catch myself several times from losing it emotionally because my heart longed for this for quite a long time. Did I mention that @vusimahlasela got up and song with them and directed Thanda in song and although I didn’t understand the language, I felt and connected with their melodies. I will never forget this day nor the time spent with my DMB Family. I’m eternally grateful. Please follow them and share them with a friend. #GodIs
